main event: Radar observed an unidentified target travel through a distance of approximately 20-25 miles in about 15 minutes, moving very fast and making sharp turns.
interesting points: The unidentified target was moving at an extremely high speed and exhibited high maneuverability, making it difficult to track.
No aircraft were identified in the area according to air traffic control radar.
The sighting occurred in Dagmar, Montana on September 28, 1963.
The unidentified target was described as roundish and bluish-white in color.
There were multiple civilian witnesses to the sighting, but their reliability was unknown.
